The '''Badzhui''' are a sup-group of the [[Shugnan]], although sometimes considered to be a distinct ethnographic group.  They are primarily [[Ismaili Muslims]], much like the Shugnan. <ref>Wixman, Ronald. ''The Peoples of the USSR: An Ethnographic Handbook'' (Armonk: M. E. Sharpe, 1984), 19.</ref> The Badzhui are also known under the generic term [[Pamiri people| Pamir people]].<ref>Olson, James Stuart.'' An Ethnohistorical Dictionary of China'' (Westport: Greenwood Press, 1998), 273-274.</ref>

