'''Ngulu''' is a [[Bantu languages|Bantu]] language spoken in east-central [[Tanzania]]. In 1987 the Ngulu-speaking population was estimated to number 132,000 [http://www.ethnologue.com/show_country.asp?name=TZ]. The Ngulu language is also called Geja, Kingulu, Nguru, Nguu, or Wayomba.
